cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically in the area of place recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions visual SLAM systems, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of a convolutional neural network for training suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training the network with triplets of images, which is a common technique in siamese networks, indicating that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
